## MIME Renderer Extensions

MIME renderers are **frontend-only** ‚Äî no backend code needed.

### Renderer Implementation

Create your renderer class in `src/renderer.ts`:

**‚úÖ Do**: Extend `Widget` and implement `IRenderMime.IRenderer`
- Set `mimeTypes` for the MIME types you handle
- Specify `dataType`: `'json'`, `'string'`, or `'object'`
- Set `safe: true` if your renderer can produce useful, sanitized output when rendering untrusted notebook data. Examples: text, images, video, audio, JSON data visualizations.
- Set `safe: false` if your renderer needs to execute code or render active content (HTML with scripts, interactive widgets). These will show "Run cell to view output" in untrusted notebooks and only render fully when the notebook is trusted.

**‚ùå Don't**: Skip security checks or render untrusted HTML without sanitization

**Security Note**: According to the [JupyterLab API docs](https://jupyterlab.readthedocs.io/en/latest/api/interfaces/rendermime-interfaces.IRenderMime.IRendererFactory.html#safe), all renderers must handle untrusted data safely. The `safe` flag indicates whether the sanitized output will be useful (`safe: true`) or if it should show a "Run cell to view output" message instead (`safe: false`). When uncertain about which to use, ask the prompter about the MIME type's capabilities and whether sanitized output would be useful.

### Widget Structure

Implement in `src/renderer.ts`:

```ts
import { IRenderMime } from '@jupyterlab/rendermime-interfaces';
import { Widget } from '@lumino/widgets';

class MyRenderer extends Widget implements IRenderMime.IRenderer {
  constructor(options: IRenderMime.IRendererOptions) {
    super();
    this.addClass('myext-Renderer');
  }
  async renderModel(model: IRenderMime.IMimeModel): Promise<void> {
    const data = model.data['text/plain'] as string;
    this.node.textContent = data;
  }
}

const extension: IRenderMime.IExtension = {
  id: '<your-ext-name>:renderer',
  rendererFactory: {
    safe: true,  // Safe: sanitized text output is useful even in untrusted notebooks
    mimeTypes: ['text/plain'],
    createRenderer: opts => new MyRenderer(opts)
  },
  rank: 50,
  dataType: 'string'
};

export default extension;
```

### Security and Performance

**‚úÖ Do**: Follow these guidelines in `src/renderer.ts`
- Namespace CSS classes: `.jp-{{ python_name | replace('_', '-') }}-renderer { ... }`
- Keep `renderModel()` fast and non-blocking
- Use async operations for expensive work

**‚ùå Don't**:
- Inject HTML without sanitization (use DOMPurify if needed)
- Mutate global styles or block the main thread
- Set `safe: true` for renderers that execute code or render active HTML/scripts ‚Äî use `safe: false` instead
